This document includes:

    * General information
    * Licensing
    * Requirements
    * Other components of GNOME
    * Extending the documentation
    * Reporting bugs

*	General information	*

   These are the GNOME libraries, the foundation for most of the
applications of the GNOME project.

*	Licensing		*

   The GNOME libraries (libgnome, libgnomeui, gtk-xmhtml, zvt, vfs)
are released under the terms of the LGPL license. Please read the file
COPYING.LIB for more information.

The rest of the code is released under the terms of the GPL license.
Please read the file COPYING for more information.

This software is copyrighted by the respective authors of the individual
modules. Please read the header and source files for details.

*	Requirements		*

To compile the GNOME libraries, as a minimum you must install:

	- GNU gettext 0.10.35                    ; gettext --version

	   ftp://prep.ai.mit.edu/pub/gnu

	- Gtk+ 1.2.xx                            ; gtk-config --version

	   ftp://ftp.gimp.org/pub/gtk/

	- DB 1.85, or DB 2.x with 1.86 compatibility enabled

	  http://www.sleepycat.com/

	- gdk-pixbuf				 ; gdk-pixbuf-config --version

	  ftp://ftp.gnome.org/pub/GNOME/stable/sources/gdk-pixbuf/

	- ORBit 0.5.xxx                          ; ls -l /usr/lib/libORBit.so.*

	  ftp://ftp.gnome.org/pub/GNOME/stable/sources/ORBit/

*	Documentation		*

Please visit http://www.gnome.org/gdp/ for more information on the
GNOME documentation project.

*	Reporting bugs		*

   To report bugs on the GNOME system: either compilation problems,
or malfunctions in the code, please do use the "gnome-bug" program
(distributed in this package).

   You can keep track of your bug, by checking the http://bugs.gnome.org/
web site.
